1
00:00:04,997 --> 00:00:08,965
[♪♪♪]

2
00:01:19,605 --> 00:01:21,249
SUPERMAN: Personal journal.

3
00:01:21,273 --> 00:01:22,951
After following the coordinates

4
00:01:22,975 --> 00:01:24,919
from my ship's initial flight recorder,

5
00:01:24,943 --> 00:01:26,988
I've finally retraced the ship's escape route

6
00:01:27,012 --> 00:01:29,323
from my home planet:

7
00:01:29,347 --> 00:01:30,581
Krypton.

8
00:01:37,106 --> 00:01:39,756
[BEEPING]

9
00:01:47,282 --> 00:01:48,960
Nothing.

10
00:01:48,984 --> 00:01:51,963
There's nothing out there but death.

11
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:53,753
[LOUD BEEPING]

12
00:01:55,307 --> 00:01:56,417
A distress signal,

13
00:01:56,441 --> 00:01:59,609
coming from the edge of the system.

14
00:02:43,522 --> 00:02:46,156
No traces of Kryptonite radiation.

15
00:02:46,925 --> 00:02:48,158
Let's drop in.

16
00:03:19,858 --> 00:03:22,826
[BEEPING]

17
00:04:26,842 --> 00:04:29,475
[HUMMING]

18
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:35,833
[HUMMING]

19
00:04:49,598 --> 00:04:53,528
I am Kala In-Ze, chief physician of Argo City.

20
00:04:53,552 --> 00:04:56,330
Five years ago,

21
00:04:56,354 --> 00:05:01,186
Argo was a thriving, vibrant world.

22
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:03,521
But then, without warning,

23
00:05:03,545 --> 00:05:05,390
KALA: <i>our sister planet, Krypton,</i>

24
00:05:05,414 --> 00:05:09,166
<i>was destroyed in a giant chain of explosions.</i>

25
00:05:13,672 --> 00:05:16,956
<i>Krypton's destruction tore Argo from its orbit.</i>

26
00:05:32,241 --> 00:05:35,720
<i>The resulting devastation destroyed most of our world</i>

27
00:05:35,744 --> 00:05:37,388
<i>and sent it moving slowly,</i>

28
00:05:37,412 --> 00:05:39,946
<i>inexorably, away from our sun...</i>

29
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:47,115
<i>leaving a few desperate survivors</i>

30
00:05:47,139 --> 00:05:49,472
<i>slowly freezing to death.</i>

31
00:05:51,643 --> 00:05:54,038
<i>There was nothing my people could do</i>

32
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:57,241
<i>but pray our distress signals would be answered.</i>

33
00:05:57,265 --> 00:06:00,328
But now, I can wait no longer.

34
00:06:00,352 --> 00:06:03,147
I have taken a desperate last chance

35
00:06:03,171 --> 00:06:05,450
to save my surviving family.

36
00:06:05,474 --> 00:06:08,653
To my knowledge, we are all that is left of Argo.

37
00:06:08,677 --> 00:06:09,943
Please help us.

38
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:51,067
I'm too late.

39
00:07:02,948 --> 00:07:04,247
Maybe not.

40
00:07:09,221 --> 00:07:11,733
WEATHERMAN [OVER TV]: <i>It's gonna be a gorgeous spring day</i>

41
00:07:11,757 --> 00:07:12,934
<i>in the nation's heartland,</i>

42
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:15,136
<i>with temperatures reaching the high 70s.</i>

43
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,439
<i>So all you folks in Smallville, Kansas,</i>

44
00:07:17,463 --> 00:07:20,580
<i>get out there and enjoy that great, big, beautiful sun.</i>

45
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:48,808
[GEESE HONKING]

46
00:08:24,012 --> 00:08:25,211
Hey!

47
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,144
That's enough of that, Kara.

48
00:08:30,168 --> 00:08:32,213
Hey, Clark. It was such a nice day,

49
00:08:32,237 --> 00:08:34,415
I thought I'd just, you know, "vroom."

50
00:08:34,439 --> 00:08:35,733
What did we talk about?

51
00:08:35,757 --> 00:08:38,185
No "vroom" during the daytime.

52
00:08:38,209 --> 00:08:39,653
I'm sorry, Clark.

53
00:08:39,677 --> 00:08:42,323
I mean, it's great staying here with your folks and everything,

54
00:08:42,347 --> 00:08:44,158
but I feel so cooped up.

55
00:08:44,182 --> 00:08:46,493
I understand, believe me.

56
00:08:46,517 --> 00:08:48,529
On Argo I dreamed about saving my mother

57
00:08:48,553 --> 00:08:49,747
and helping my friends.

58
00:08:49,771 --> 00:08:52,083
And now that I have the power to help people,

59
00:08:52,107 --> 00:08:53,400
why won't you let me?

60
00:08:53,424 --> 00:08:55,720
You need to adjust to life here a little bit more.

61
00:08:55,744 --> 00:08:56,909
Just be patient.

62
00:08:58,045 --> 00:08:59,990
So, Clark, will you be staying the night?

63
00:09:00,014 --> 00:09:02,843
Sorry, Ma, Metropolis is having a sudden crime wave.

64
00:09:02,867 --> 00:09:05,346
Yeah, I saw on TV that Intergang's back.

65
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:07,315
Intergang? What's that?

66
00:09:07,339 --> 00:09:08,850
Nothing you have to worry about.

67
00:09:08,874 --> 00:09:10,768
Who's worried? I was just asking.

68
00:09:10,792 --> 00:09:13,354
They're a bunch of hoodlums with terrible weapons.

69
00:09:13,378 --> 00:09:14,421
Oh, yeah?

70
00:09:14,445 --> 00:09:16,190
They caused Clark no end of trouble.

71
00:09:16,214 --> 00:09:17,191
Really?

72
00:09:17,215 --> 00:09:19,193
Thanks, guys. I gotta go.

73
00:09:19,217 --> 00:09:20,194
You be good.

74
00:09:20,218 --> 00:09:23,336
Yeah, yeah. Feet on the ground, I know.

75
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:28,391
So, Pa, Intergang, huh?

76
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:34,208
We got a new Intergang running riot through town,

77
00:09:34,232 --> 00:09:35,793
and what does Perry ask me to cover?

78
00:09:35,817 --> 00:09:38,034
Some techno geek show.

79
00:09:42,908 --> 00:09:46,037
Somehow I don't smell Pulitzer here.

80
00:09:46,061 --> 00:09:47,137
Ooh.

81
00:09:47,161 --> 00:09:48,155
[SNIFFS]

82
00:09:48,179 --> 00:09:49,924
Or soap, for that matter.

83
00:09:49,948 --> 00:09:52,627
Oh, at least the chief treats you like a real reporter.

84
00:09:52,651 --> 00:09:54,328
I mean, when's he gonna give me a break?

85
00:09:54,352 --> 00:09:57,481
First rule of reporting, kid: never count on breaks.

86
00:09:57,505 --> 00:09:59,767
You want a story? Go get one.

87
00:09:59,791 --> 00:10:01,402
It won't just drop in your lap.

88
00:10:01,426 --> 00:10:03,070
[GLASS SHATTERING]

89
00:10:03,094 --> 00:10:04,760
[CROWD GASPING]

90
00:10:05,764 --> 00:10:09,899
[PEOPLE GASPING, SCREAMING]

91
00:10:13,221 --> 00:10:14,854
I stand corrected.

92
00:10:21,345 --> 00:10:25,930
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

93
00:10:34,475 --> 00:10:37,493
WOMAN: No, no!

94
00:10:40,031 --> 00:10:42,009
WOMAN 2: Get out of the way!

95
00:10:42,033 --> 00:10:43,265
Let's go!

96
00:10:45,736 --> 00:10:47,419
They're heading back outside.

97
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:55,594
[SIREN WAILING]

98
00:10:56,964 --> 00:10:58,442
Freeze! Or we'll fire!

99
00:10:58,466 --> 00:11:01,111
Tell you what, rent-a-cops, you freeze...

100
00:11:01,135 --> 00:11:03,335
[BOTH GRUNTING]

101
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:06,283
And we'll fire!

102
00:11:06,307 --> 00:11:08,273
[GUARDS SHOUTING]

103
00:11:10,678 --> 00:11:13,590
You see, Metropolis, nobody can beat Intergang!

104
00:11:13,614 --> 00:11:14,724
Nobody!

105
00:11:14,748 --> 00:11:16,831
Well, then, just call me "nobody."

106
00:11:20,188 --> 00:11:21,165
Let him have it.

107
00:11:21,189 --> 00:11:22,332
[GRUNTS]

108
00:11:22,356 --> 00:11:24,334
[GROANING]

109
00:11:24,358 --> 00:11:25,374
Dump it!

110
00:11:30,264 --> 00:11:31,397
[GROANS]

111
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:40,172
[GROANING]

112
00:11:44,761 --> 00:11:46,278
[SCREAMS]

113
00:11:52,887 --> 00:11:57,555
[GROANING]

114
00:12:15,509 --> 00:12:16,920
Whoa!

115
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:18,877
[ELECTRICITY ZAPPING]

116
00:12:25,803 --> 00:12:27,781
[GASPS]

117
00:12:27,805 --> 00:12:28,949
Hey, Supes!

118
00:12:28,973 --> 00:12:29,949
Catch!

119
00:12:29,973 --> 00:12:31,823
[SCREAMING]

120
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:38,897
Let's get the heck out of here!

121
00:12:40,935 --> 00:12:44,386
[SCREAMING]

122
00:12:47,241 --> 00:12:50,242
From now on, I'll leave the flying to you.

123
00:12:58,786 --> 00:13:03,600
[PLAYING ROCK MUSIC]

124
00:13:03,624 --> 00:13:06,236
Yeah! We took Superman on and trashed him!

125
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:08,505
Excuse me, who trashed him?

126
00:13:08,529 --> 00:13:11,475
Excuse me, who did he slam into a parked car?

127
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:15,779
GRANNY: Now, now, what's all this fluttering, my ducklings?

128
00:13:15,803 --> 00:13:19,616
Your loving Granny doesn't like her babies to quarrel.

129
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,334
BOTH: Yes, Granny.

130
00:13:21,358 --> 00:13:24,287
An obedient family is a happy family,

131
00:13:24,311 --> 00:13:29,293
and a happy family means a happy Granny.

132
00:13:29,317 --> 00:13:31,133
ALL: Yes, Granny.

133
00:13:34,822 --> 00:13:35,899
WOMAN: <i>Mr. Kent.</i>

134
00:13:35,923 --> 00:13:36,917
Yes?

135
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,368
<i>Your cousin to see you.</i>

136
00:13:38,392 --> 00:13:40,125
Cousin?

137
00:13:43,831 --> 00:13:45,058
It's me, Kara.

138
00:13:45,082 --> 00:13:46,143
I know.

139
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:48,150
You saw through my secret identity?

140
00:13:49,420 --> 00:13:50,985
Ah!

141
00:13:52,173 --> 00:13:53,883
How'd you get here?

142
00:13:53,907 --> 00:13:56,820
You told me not to "vroom," so I ran.

143
00:13:56,844 --> 00:13:59,356
Listen, I saw a report about Intergang on TV,

144
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:01,241
and I thought you could really use my help.

145
00:14:01,265 --> 00:14:03,309
Look, I appreciate your concern, Kara,

146
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:05,112
but I don't want you to rush into something

147
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:06,329
you're not ready for.

148
00:14:06,353 --> 00:14:08,582
I didn't save your life so you could throw it away

149
00:14:08,606 --> 00:14:10,433
fighting some ray gun-toting punks.

150
00:14:10,457 --> 00:14:12,469
But... No buts.

151
00:14:12,493 --> 00:14:13,670
I gotta get back to work.

152
00:14:13,694 --> 00:14:15,122
Here's a key to my apartment.

153
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:16,173
Wait for me there.

154
00:14:16,197 --> 00:14:18,146
We'll talk later.

155
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,433
And walk.

156
00:14:26,874 --> 00:14:29,753
But, Lois, I was right there when Intergang hit.

157
00:14:29,777 --> 00:14:31,355
Why can't I help you with the story?

158
00:14:31,379 --> 00:14:32,622
Too dangerous.

159
00:14:32,646 --> 00:14:34,608
Stick to the darkroom, kiddo.

160
00:14:34,632 --> 00:14:35,608
But, Lois...

161
00:14:35,632 --> 00:14:37,294
Can you talk some sense into him?

162
00:14:37,318 --> 00:14:40,285
I've had my fill of teenagers today.

163
00:14:45,292 --> 00:14:47,954
Look, I think one of 'em might have dropped this.

164
00:14:47,978 --> 00:14:49,088
It's a game token.

165
00:14:49,112 --> 00:14:51,358
All we have to do is hit every video parlor

166
00:14:51,382 --> 00:14:54,210
in Metropolis... Good. You go, Jim.

167
00:14:54,234 --> 00:14:55,862
Have a free game on me.

168
00:14:55,886 --> 00:14:57,569
Okay, fine.

169
00:15:05,746 --> 00:15:07,591
She said go, I'll go.

170
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,843
She doesn't think I can do it, I'm doing it.

171
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,067
I'll just go it alone.

172
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:16,405
Can I join you?

173
00:15:27,808 --> 00:15:30,504
Nah, same size, but not the right color.

174
00:15:30,528 --> 00:15:32,511
Come on, let's try the one across the street.

175
00:15:34,765 --> 00:15:36,110
Hey, slow down.

176
00:15:36,134 --> 00:15:38,112
You said your name's Karen?

177
00:15:38,136 --> 00:15:39,112
Yeah.

178
00:15:39,136 --> 00:15:40,364
And you're an intern?

179
00:15:40,388 --> 00:15:41,498
Yeah.

180
00:15:41,522 --> 00:15:43,033
I thought I knew all the interns.

181
00:15:43,057 --> 00:15:44,968
I, uh, just started today.

182
00:15:44,992 --> 00:15:47,020
And like you, I wanted to make a good impression.

183
00:15:47,044 --> 00:15:49,094
So let's get that story.

184
00:15:59,023 --> 00:16:00,033
Bingo!

185
00:16:00,057 --> 00:16:01,151
What's that mean?

186
00:16:01,175 --> 00:16:02,670
They're the same.

187
00:16:02,694 --> 00:16:03,954
Oh, yeah.

188
00:16:03,978 --> 00:16:04,955
Bingo.

189
00:16:04,979 --> 00:16:06,090
TROUBLE: Hey, hey!

190
00:16:06,114 --> 00:16:08,092
Didn't I tell you to keep out of my way?

191
00:16:08,116 --> 00:16:10,410
Uh, hey, man, i-it was an accident.

192
00:16:10,434 --> 00:16:11,694
Just like your face.

193
00:16:11,718 --> 00:16:12,979
Chill, Trouble.

194
00:16:13,003 --> 00:16:14,181
We're in public.

195
00:16:14,205 --> 00:16:16,672
Granny wants us to be good little boys and girls.

196
00:16:21,796 --> 00:16:22,939
[SCREAMS]

197
00:16:22,963 --> 00:16:25,276
[BEEPING]

198
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,043
That guy's got some kind of laser weapon.

199
00:16:27,067 --> 00:16:28,078
What?

200
00:16:28,102 --> 00:16:29,102
Over there.

201
00:16:31,306 --> 00:16:32,766
How can you tell?

202
00:16:32,790 --> 00:16:34,285
Uh, his jacket was open.

203
00:16:34,309 --> 00:16:36,603
And you could see it from all the way over here?

204
00:16:36,627 --> 00:16:38,706
Yeah! Come on!

205
00:16:38,730 --> 00:16:41,941
Granny said she doesn't want us calling attention to ourselves.

206
00:16:41,965 --> 00:16:44,712
And you see what she does to people who break the rules.

207
00:16:44,736 --> 00:16:47,353
Ahh, I'm too smart for that old bat.

208
00:16:50,908 --> 00:16:52,369
Where do you think they're going?

209
00:16:52,393 --> 00:16:53,704
To Grandmother's house.

210
00:16:53,728 --> 00:16:54,810
Wait up!

211
00:17:10,762 --> 00:17:12,478
We're getting warmer.

212
00:17:17,101 --> 00:17:18,679
I didn't see how they opened the door.

213
00:17:18,703 --> 00:17:19,696
Did you see it?

214
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,804
Yeah, I think it was right here.

215
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:26,910
Come on!

216
00:17:29,346 --> 00:17:30,424
[DOOR CRASHES SHUT]

217
00:17:30,448 --> 00:17:31,914
Oops.

218
00:17:33,785 --> 00:17:35,834
Don't even blink.

219
00:17:38,038 --> 00:17:41,101
Now, why have you nosey, little mice come calling

220
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:43,854
on poor old Granny Goodness?

221
00:17:43,878 --> 00:17:48,091
Uh, my chick and I heard Intergang was back in biz.

222
00:17:48,115 --> 00:17:49,692
Sounded like a good gig.

223
00:17:49,716 --> 00:17:51,210
Thought we'd join up.

224
00:17:51,234 --> 00:17:52,351
Bingo!

225
00:17:53,487 --> 00:17:55,965
Let me tell you tadpoles how I work.

226
00:17:55,989 --> 00:17:58,218
I seek out the lost, little lambs

227
00:17:58,242 --> 00:18:00,970
society has cruelly abandoned.

228
00:18:00,994 --> 00:18:03,557
I take them lovingly under my wings,

229
00:18:03,581 --> 00:18:08,462
give them the power to face the cold, heartless world

230
00:18:08,486 --> 00:18:10,714
and kick its butt!

231
00:18:10,738 --> 00:18:12,883
We're in!

232
00:18:12,907 --> 00:18:15,519
But you hardly seem the type.

233
00:18:15,543 --> 00:18:20,023
So bright-eyed and soft-skinned.

234
00:18:20,047 --> 00:18:23,894
Life has not scarred you as it has my other goslings.

235
00:18:23,918 --> 00:18:27,703
Still, we can remedy that.

236
00:18:31,776 --> 00:18:33,904
All right, I've seen enough!

237
00:18:33,928 --> 00:18:35,889
Don't you realize you're being duped?

238
00:18:35,913 --> 00:18:37,390
You think you're getting power,

239
00:18:37,414 --> 00:18:40,010
but she's just turning you into her own personal goon squad.

240
00:18:40,034 --> 00:18:41,345
What are you doing?

241
00:18:41,369 --> 00:18:43,846
What do you think? I'm shutting down this psycho witch!

242
00:18:43,870 --> 00:18:46,617
Eh! Such language!

243
00:18:46,641 --> 00:18:50,637
Children, defend your Granny's honor.

244
00:18:50,661 --> 00:18:51,655
Kill her!

245
00:18:51,679 --> 00:18:53,995
[GANGSTERS GROWLING, YELLING]

246
00:19:06,461 --> 00:19:07,743
[GASPS]

247
00:19:13,384 --> 00:19:14,878
I don't believe it.

248
00:19:14,902 --> 00:19:16,613
A super... girl?

249
00:19:16,637 --> 00:19:17,664
Believe it.

250
00:19:17,688 --> 00:19:18,665
[SCREAMS]

251
00:19:18,689 --> 00:19:21,401
Oh, you naughty little monkey.

252
00:19:21,425 --> 00:19:25,210
Granny will spank you good.

253
00:19:33,404 --> 00:19:38,941
[GROANING]

254
00:19:42,145 --> 00:19:43,962
[GRANNY SCREAMING]

255
00:19:47,585 --> 00:19:49,768
Take a nap, Grandma.

256
00:19:50,454 --> 00:19:52,237
Outstanding.

257
00:19:52,823 --> 00:19:54,568
No, ho, ho, ho.

258
00:19:54,592 --> 00:19:58,227
It doesn't end that easily, my little gingersnap.

259
00:20:02,934 --> 00:20:04,578
What the heck is that?

260
00:20:04,602 --> 00:20:06,212
She's from Apokolips.

261
00:20:06,236 --> 00:20:07,414
Where?

262
00:20:07,438 --> 00:20:10,572
The surprises are just beginning, muffin.

263
00:20:17,881 --> 00:20:19,426
You called, Granny?

264
00:20:19,450 --> 00:20:22,996
Girls, this ninny-noodle wants to play rough.

265
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:26,755
Make her last moments special.

266
00:20:29,376 --> 00:20:32,143
[♪♪♪]

267
00:20:45,593 --> 00:20:49,461
[♪♪♪]

